      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@jnewbery I agree that the API should change. However I don't think that we should give each deprecated thing its own command line argument to enable or disable it. I think we could do some sort of versioning with different endpoints like what multiwallet does with multiple wallets. So we could add a `/deprecated/` endpoint for which any deprecated behavior would exist behind before being removed in the future. If you want to access deprecated stuff, you can use that endpoint, and ideally, non-deprecated stuff would also work behind that endpoint as well.",
